  <summary>7/15/1987--Introduced.
Amends part D (Child Support and Establishment of Paternity) of title IV of the Social Security Act to make it clear that the authority to withhold past-due child support from an individual's Federal tax refunds may be exercised after such child reaches the age of majority.</summary>
